Intro: An Adoring Fan has been stalking you for weeks. He's harmless but so annoying. He really needs to die.
Death: The Adoring Fan dies slowly and painfully. His last words are you're the best. Good luck on your journey.
Attack: tries to give you a hug
Miss: goes in for a hug, but you dodge aside

Intro: An Apprentice Mage appears in front of you. he begins casting a conjuration spell, but does not seem very confident.
Death: The Apprentice Conjurer dies. He probably should have studied in Winterhold a little harder.
Attack: summons a Flame Atronach, which scorches you with flames
Miss: grows frustrated as his Atronach fails to damage you

Intro: You feel an otherworldly heat. An Apprentice Fire Mage stands before you. he seems unsure of his skills.
Death: The Apprentice Fire Mage dies. He probably should have studied in Winterhold a little harder.
Attack: releases jets of flame from his hands

Intro: An unnatural coldness creeps over you. An Apprentice Ice Mage stands before you. he seems unsure of his skills.
Death: The Apprentice Ice Mage dies. He probably should have studied in Winterhold a little harder.
Attack: releases streams of frost from his hands

Intro: A young mage appears in front of you. He smells of death. It's a Necromancer!
Death: You expand the Necromancer's knowledge of death by providing them with invaluable first hand experience on the topic.
Attack: commands his reanimated skeever to attack you
Miss: commands his zombie skeever to attack, but it misses

Intro: Your hair stands on end. An Apprentice Storm Mage stands before you. he seems unsure of his skills.
Death: The Apprentice Storm Mage dies. He probably should have studied in Winterhold a little harder.
Attack: unleashes a torrent of lightning from his palm

Intro: An eerie blue light fills the area; an Ascendant Necromancer is raising the dead to attack you.
Death: You expand Ascendant Necromancer's knowledge of death by providing them with invaluable first hand experience on the topic.
Attack: commands a reanimated zombie to attack you

Intro: A Bandit leaps out in front of you. He won't let you leave without a fight.
Death: He cries out and expires. He died as he lived. Or something like that.

Intro: Suddenly, a Bandit Highwayman jumps out at you. He's demanding coin for you to pass.
Death: he cries out and expires. He died as he lived. Or something like that.

Intro: A Bandit Marauder charges at you, weapon drawn. He doesn't seem like a chatty fellow.
Death: he cries out and expires. He died as he lived. Or something like that.

Intro: A Bandit Outlaw is sipping mead at a table. He attacks in a drunken rage.
Death: he cries out and expires. He died as he lived. Or something like that.
Attack: Jabs his dagger into your armor

Intro: A Bandit Plunderer is raiding corpses ahead of you. He can't wait to count out your coin.
Death: he cries out and expires. He died as he lived. Or something like that.

Intro: A Bandit Thug is talking to himself up ahead. He smashes his mead bottle and charges you wildly.
Death: he cries out and expires. He died as he lived. Or something like that.
Kill: Before your dying body begins to cool, the Bandit Thug starts going through your belongings.

Intro: You hear a scary growl. It's a bear! Apparently you smell like a giant piece of salmon coated in honey.
Death: The Bear roars defiantly before collapsing, dead.

Intro: A blast of fire scorches the ground in front of you. You look up and see a Blood Dragon ready for battle.
Death: The Blood Dragon crashes to the ground, plowing a path with its dead body.
Attack: takes a swing at you with its massive claws
Miss: attacks, but you leap out of the way
Kill: The Blood Dragon has defeated you. It roars in triumph. So much for being the 'one they fear'.

Intro: A Cave Bear is sniffing around up ahead. It doesn't look like an herbivore.
Death: The Cave Bear roars defiantly before collapsing, dead.
Kill: Brutally mauled, you die at the paws of the Cave Bear.

Intro: A horrible chittering sound fills the air. A Chaurus attacks!
Death: Your weapon cracks the Chaurus's chitin and venomous blood seeps from its dead body.
Miss: jabs at you, but you parry the blow

Intro: You hear a familiar chittering. You see a Chaurus Reaper approaching, stinger covered in poison.
Death: Your weapon cracks the Chaurus Reaper's chitin and venomous blood seeps from its dead body.
Miss: jabs at you, but you parry the blow

Intro: A Conjurer is summoning a creature in front of you. Best not let him finish.
Death: The arcane Conjurer falls to your weapon. As they say, live by the magicka, die by the blade, right?
Attack: summons a Frost Atronach to attack you
Miss: commands his Frost Atronach to attack, but it misses

Intro: A Dark Brotherhood Assassin appears from the shadows, ready to claim a contract on your life. he whispers, 'We know.'
Death: he falls dead, his soul free to join Sithis in the Void.

Intro: A skulking Death Hound growls at you. His master may be close by.
Death: The Death Hound whimpers and dies.

Intro: A deranged Khajiit looks at you with wild eyes, like a kitten staring at a ball of yarn. Which makes sense, you suppose.
Death: he dies with a sad meow.

Intro: A Disgraced City Guard stumbles toward you, drunk on mead and looking for a fight. No wonder he got fired.
Death: he screams and dies, as pathetically as he lived.

Intro: You hear a loud roar, then flapping wings. It's a Dragon! Now this is an epic battle. Dovah versus Dovahkiin.
Death: The Dragon crashes to the ground, plowing a path with its dead body.
Attack: blasts you with its flaming breath
Miss: attempts to roast you but you leap out of the way
Kill: The Dragon has defeated you. It roars in triumph. So much for being the

Intro: A Draugr Overlord, clad in Ebony armor, awakens from its slumber. It looks strong.
Death: The Draugr Overlord collapses to the ground, at long last given true eternal rest.
Attack: strikes you with its ancient sword
Miss: attacks, but you parry the blow

Intro: The way is blocked by a Draugr Scourge. His soulless eyes look hungry.
Death: The Draugr Scourge collapses to the ground, at long last given true eternal rest.
Attack: sends a spike of ice at you
Kill: The undead eyes of the Draugr Scourge glow with undead power as you die at its hands.

Intro: A Draugr Scourge Lord stands in your path. You're really starting to wish the Nords cremated their dead.
Attack: blasts you with a frost breath shout
Kill: The undead eyes of the Draugr Scourge Lord glow with undead power as you die at its hands.

Intro: A Draugr Thrall blocks the way. Something hidden is controlling it. And that something wants you dead.
Death: The Draugr Thrall collapses to the ground, at long last given true eternal rest.
Attack: strikes you with its ancient sword
Miss: attacks, but you parry the blow

Intro: The corpse of an ancient Nord rises up before you; it's a Draugr Warrior.
Death: The Draugr Warrior collapses to the ground, at long last given true eternal rest.
Attack: strikes you with its ancient sword

Intro: A Draugr Wight lurches out of his grave. It stinks of rotting flesh.
Death: The Draugr Wight collapses to the ground, at long last given true eternal rest.
Attack: strikes you with its ancient sword
Miss: attacks, but you parry the blow

Intro: A Dremora Caitiff has been summoned ahead. He smells weakness in you.
Death: The Dremora Caitiff dies with a curse on its lips, unable to escape through Daedric portal it summoned.
Miss: attacks, but you evade his maneuver
Kill: 'There could be no other end,' the Dremora Caitiff intones as darkness consumes you.

Intro: A brutish Dremora Churl awaits you. He laughs maniacally.
Death: The Dremora Churl dies with a curse on its lips, unable to escape through Daedric portal it summoned.
Attack: blasts a stream of fire towards you

Intro: A Dremora Kynreeve blocks the way. He asks if you seek death, mortal.
Death: The Dremora Kynreeve dies with a curse on its lips, unable to escape through Daedric portal it summoned.
Kill: 'There could be no other end,' the Dremora Kynreeve intones as darkness consumes you.

Intro: A challenger is near - it appears to be a Dremora Kynval.
Death: The Dremora Kynval dies with a curse on its lips, unable to escape through Daedric portal it summoned.
Kill: 'There could be no other end,' the Dremora Kynval intones as darkness consumes you.

Intro: A pale form emerges slowly from the darkness. It's a Falmer. It may be blind, but it heard you.
Death: This blind Falmer has lived darkness and died as it lived.

Intro: A Falmer Gloomlurker blocks your path. He looks like he doesn't get much sun.
Death: This blind Falmer Gloomlurker has lived darkness and died as it lived.
Kill: The Falmer Gloomlurker's attack drops you to the ground. It starts dragging you by the ankle into the darkness.

Intro: A Falmer Nightprowler has been following you. He leaps out to attack.
Death: This blind Falmer Nightprowler has lived darkness and died as it lived.

Intro: You hear dragging feet ahead. A Falmer Skulker with a nasty looking weapon blocks your path.
Death: This blind Falmer Skulker has lived darkness and died as it lived.
Miss: shoots, but you block it with your shield

Intro: A blast of heat blows by your face. A Fire Mage stands before you.
Death: The arcane Fire Mage falls to your weapon. As they say, live by the magicka, die by the blade, right?

Intro: The room brightens up with an otherworldly light; a Flame Atronach twists in the air blocking your path.
Death: The Flame Atronach is cast back into Oblivion.
Attack: hurls a ball of fire at you
Miss: misses you with a ball of fire

Intro: A wild eyed Forsworn blocks your path. He looks tough, and totally psychotic.
Death: The Forsworn looks up at you and promises that three more will rise in his place, right before you decapitate him.

Intro: Someone is rummaging through a container. It's a Forsworn Forager! She wants a fight.
Death: The Forsworn Forager looks up at you and promises that three more will rise in her place, right before you decapitate her.

Intro: A Forsworn Looter is searching through some corpses ahead. He looks like he'd like to search yours next.
Death: The Forsworn Looter looks up at you and promises that three more will rise in his place, right before you decapitate him.

Intro: A wild eyed Forsworn pillager leaps out at you, snarling. His blades are as ugly and angry as he is.
Death: The Forsworn Pillager looks up at you and promises that three more will rise in his place, right before you decapitate him.
Kill: You fall to your knees, defeated. The Forsworn Pillager looms over you, ready to sacrifice you to the Old Gods.

Intro: A mountain of ice stands between you and the way forward. It's a Frost Atronach. Lovely.
Death: The Frost Atronach is cast back into Oblivion.
Attack: launches deadly ice in your direction
Miss: misses you with an ice spike
Kill: The Frost Atronach slams its icy body into you, freezing you on contact.

Intro: You see a Frost Troll charging through the storm, and he looks angry.
Kill: The Frost Troll's last attack proves fatal. It howls in victory.

Intro: A suspicious stone statue lies in front of you. Suddenly, the Gargoyle awakens! Time to rock. Literally.
